  38,1,"ŠĻĘ√£d. By the Quran, full of reminders"
  38,2,"ňĻThis is the truth,ňļ yet the disbelievers are ňĻentrenchedňļ in arrogance and opposition"
  38,3,"ňĻImagineňļ how many peoples We destroyed before them, and they cried out when it was too late to escape"
  38,4,"Now, the pagans are astonished that a warner has come to them from among themselves.¬†And the disbelievers say, ‚ÄúThis is a magician, a total liar"
  38,5,"Has he reduced ňĻallňļ the gods to One God? Indeed, this is something totally astonishing.‚ÄĚ"
  38,6,"The chiefs among them went forth saying, ‚ÄúCarry on, and stand firm in devotion to your gods. Certainly this is just a scheme ňĻfor powerňļ"
  38,7,We have never heard of this in the previous faith.¬†This is nothing but a fabrication
  38,8,"Has the Reminder been revealed ňĻonlyňļ to him out of ňĻall ofňļ us?‚ÄĚ In fact, they are ňĻonlyňļ in doubt of My ňĻrevealedňļ Reminder.¬†In fact, ňĻthey do so becauseňļ they have not yet tasted My punishment"
  38,9,"Or ňĻis it becauseňļ they possess the treasuries of the mercy of your Lord‚ÄĒthe Almighty, the Giver ňĻof all bountiesňļ"
  38,10,"Or ňĻis it becauseňļ the kingdom of the heavens and the earth and everything in between belongs to them? Let them then climb their way ňĻto heaven, if their claim is trueňļ"
  38,11,This is just another ňĻenemyňļ force bound for defeat out there
  38,12,"Before them, the people of Noah denied ňĻthe truthňļ, as did ‚Äô√ād, Pharaoh of the mighty structures"
  38,13,"Tham√Ľd, the people of Lot, and the residents of the Forest.¬†These were ňĻallňļ enemy forces"
  38,14,"Each rejected their messenger, so My punishment was justified"
  38,15,These ňĻpagansňļ are awaiting nothing but a single Blast that cannot be stopped
  38,16,"They say ňĻmockinglyňļ, ‚ÄúOur Lord! Hasten for us our share ňĻof the punishmentňļ before the Day of Reckoning.‚ÄĚ"
  38,17,"Be patient ňĻO Prophetňļ with what they say. And remember Our servant, David, the man of strength. Indeed, he ňĻconstantlyňļ turned ňĻto Allahňļ"
  38,18,We truly subjected the mountains to hymn ňĻOur praisesňļ along with him in the evening and after sunrise
  38,19,"And ňĻWe subjectedňļ the birds, flocking together. All turned to him ňĻechoing his hymnsňļ"
  38,20,"We strengthened his kingship, and gave him wisdom and sound judgment"
  38,21,"Has the story of the two plaintiffs, who scaled the ňĻwall of David‚Äôsňļ sanctuary, reached you ňĻO Prophetňļ"
  38,22,"When they came into David‚Äôs presence, he was startled by them. They said, ‚ÄúHave no fear. ňĻWe are merelyňļ two in a dispute: one of us has wronged the other. So judge between us with truth‚ÄĒdo not go beyond ňĻitňļ‚ÄĒand guide us to the right way"
  38,23,"This is my brother.¬†He has ninety-nine sheep while I have ňĻonlyňļ one. ňĻStillňļ he asked me to give it up to him, overwhelming me with ňĻhisňļ argument.‚ÄĚ"
  38,24,"David ňĻeventuallyňļ ruled, ‚ÄúHe has definitely wronged you in demanding ňĻto addňļ your sheep to his. And certainly many partners wrong each other, except those who believe and do good‚ÄĒbut how few are they!‚ÄĚ Then David realized that We had tested him so he asked for his Lord‚Äôs forgiveness, fell down in prostration, and turned ňĻto Him in repentanceňļ"
  38,25,So We forgave that for him. And he will indeed have ňĻa status ofňļ closeness to Us and an honourable destination
  38,26,"ňĻWe instructed him:ňļ ‚ÄúO David! We have surely made you an authority in the land, so judge between people with truth. And do not follow ňĻyourňļ desires or they will lead you astray from Allah‚Äôs Way. Surely those who go astray from Allah‚Äôs Way will suffer a severe punishment for neglecting the Day of Reckoning.‚ÄĚ"
  38,27,We have not created the heavens and earth and everything in between without purpose‚ÄĒas the disbelievers think. So woe to the disbelievers because of the Fire
  38,28,Or should We treat those who believe and do good like those who make mischief throughout the land? Or should We treat the righteous like the wicked
  38,29,"ňĻThis isňļ a blessed Book which We have revealed to you ňĻO Prophetňļ so that they may contemplate its verses, and people of reason may be mindful"
  38,30,"And We blessed David with Solomon‚ÄĒwhat an excellent servant ňĻhe wasňļ! Indeed, he ňĻconstantlyňļ turned ňĻto Allahňļ"
  38,31,"ňĻRememberňļ when the well-trained, swift horses were paraded before him in the evening"
  38,32,"He then proclaimed, ‚ÄúI am truly in love with ňĻtheseňļ fine things out of remembrance for Allah,‚ÄĚ until they went out of sight"
  38,33,"ňĻHe ordered,ňļ ‚ÄúBring them back to me!‚ÄĚ Then he began to rub down their legs and necks"
  38,34,"And indeed, We tested Solomon, placing a ňĻdeformedňļ body on his throne,¬†then he turned ňĻto Allah in repentanceňļ"
  38,35,"He prayed, ‚ÄúMy Lord! Forgive me, and grant me an authority that will never be matched by anyone after me. You are indeed the Giver ňĻof all bountiesňļ.‚ÄĚ"
  38,36,"So We subjected to him the wind, blowing gently at his command to wherever he pleased"
  38,37,And ňĻWe subjected to himňļ every builder and diver¬†of the jinn
  38,38,and others bound together in chains
  38,39,"ňĻAllah said,ňļ ‚ÄúThis is Our gift, so give or withhold ňĻas you wishňļ, never to be called to account.‚ÄĚ"
  38,40,And he will indeed have ňĻa status ofňļ closeness to Us and an honourable destination
  38,41,"And remember Our servant Job, when he cried out to his Lord, ‚ÄúSatan has afflicted me with distress and suffering.‚ÄĚ"
  38,42,"ňĻWe responded,ňļ ‚ÄúStomp your foot: ňĻnowňļ here is a cool ňĻand refreshingňļ spring for washing and drinking.‚ÄĚ"
  38,43,"And We gave him back his family, twice as many, as a mercy from Us and a lesson for people of reason"
  38,44,"ňĻAnd We said to him,ňļ ‚ÄúTake in your hand a bundle of grass, and strike ňĻyour wifeňļ with it, and do not break your oath.‚ÄĚ¬†We truly found him patient. What an excellent servant ňĻhe wasňļ! Indeed, he ňĻconstantlyňļ turned ňĻto Allahňļ"
  38,45,"And remember Our servants: Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob‚ÄĒthe men of strength and insight"
  38,46,We truly chose them for the honour of proclaiming the Hereafter
  38,47,And in Our sight they are truly among the chosen and the finest
  38,48,"Also remember Ishmael, Elisha, and ‚Īęul-Kifl.¬†All are among the best"
  38,49,This is ňĻallňļ a reminder. And the righteous will certainly have an honourable destination
  38,50,"the Gardens of Eternity, whose gates will be open for them"
  38,51,"There they will recline, calling for abundant fruit and drink"
  38,52,And with them will be maidens of modest gaze and equal age
  38,53,This is what you are promised for the Day of Reckoning
  38,54,This is indeed Our provision that will never end
  38,55,That is that. And the transgressors will certainly have the worst destination
  38,56,"Hell, where they will burn. What an evil place to rest"
  38,57,"Let them then taste this: boiling water and ňĻoozingňļ pus"
  38,58,and other torments of the same sort
  38,59,"ňĻThe misleaders will say to one another,ňļ ‚ÄúHere is a crowd ňĻof followersňļ being thrown in with us. They are not welcome, ňĻforňļ they ňĻtooňļ will burn in the Fire.‚ÄĚ"
  38,60,"The followers will respond, ‚ÄúNo! You are not welcome! You brought this upon us. What an evil place for settlement!‚ÄĚ"
  38,61,"Adding, ‚ÄúOur Lord! Whoever brought this upon us, double their punishment in the Fire.‚ÄĚ"
  38,62,"The tyrants will ask ňĻone anotherňļ, ‚ÄúBut why do we not see those we considered to be lowly"
  38,63,Were we wrong in mocking them ňĻin the worldňļ?¬†Or do our eyes ňĻjustňļ fail to see them ňĻin the Fireňļ?‚ÄĚ
  38,64,This dispute between the residents of the Fire will certainly come to pass
  38,65,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúI am only a warner. And there is no god ňĻworthy of worshipňļ except Allah‚ÄĒthe One, the Supreme"
  38,66,"ňĻHe is theňļ Lord of the heavens and the earth and everything in between‚ÄĒthe Almighty, Most Forgiving.‚ÄĚ"
  38,67,"Say, ‚ÄúThis ňĻQuranňļ is momentous news"
  38,68,from which you ňĻpagansňļ are turning away.‚ÄĚ
  38,69,"ňĻAnd say,ňļ ‚ÄúI had no knowledge of the highest assembly ňĻin heavenňļ when they differed ňĻconcerning Adamňļ"
  38,70,What is revealed to me is that I am only sent with a clear warning.‚ÄĚ
  38,71,"ňĻRemember, O Prophetňļ when your Lord said to the angels, ‚ÄúI am going to create a human being from clay"
  38,72,"So when I have fashioned him and had a spirit of My Own ňĻcreationňļ breathed into him, fall down in prostration to him.‚ÄĚ"
  38,73,So the angels prostrated all together‚ÄĒ
  38,74,"but not Ibl√ģs,¬†who acted arrogantly,¬†becoming unfaithful"
  38,75,"Allah asked, ‚ÄúO Ibl√ģs! What prevented you from prostrating to what I created with My Own Hands? Did you ňĻjustňļ become proud? Or have you always been arrogant?‚ÄĚ"
  38,76,"He replied, ‚ÄúI am better than he is: You created me from fire and him from clay.‚ÄĚ"
  38,77,"Allah commanded, ‚ÄúThen get out of Paradise, for you are truly cursed"
  38,78,And surely upon you is My condemnation until the Day of Judgment.‚ÄĚ
  38,79,"Satan appealed, ‚ÄúMy Lord! Then delay my end until the Day of their resurrection.‚ÄĚ"
