  38,86,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúI do not ask you for any reward for this ňĻQuranňļ, nor do I pretend to be someone I am not"
  38,87,It is only a reminder to the whole world
  38,88,And you will certainly know its truth before long.‚ÄĚ
  39,1,"The revelation of this Book is from Allah‚ÄĒthe Almighty, All-Wise"
  39,2,"Indeed, We have sent down the Book to you ňĻO Prophetňļ in truth, so worship Allah ňĻaloneňļ, being sincerely devoted to Him"
  39,3,"Indeed, sincere devotion is due ňĻonlyňļ to Allah. As for those who take other lords besides Him, ňĻsaying,ňļ ‚ÄúWe worship them only so they may bring us closer to Allah,‚ÄĚ surely Allah will judge between all¬†regarding what they differed about. Allah certainly does not guide whoever persists in lying and disbelief"
  39,4,"Had it been Allah‚Äôs Will to have offspring, He could have chosen whatever He willed of His creation. Glory be to Him! He is Allah‚ÄĒthe One, the Supreme"
  39,5,"He created the heavens and the earth for a purpose. He wraps the night around the day, and wraps the day around the night. And He has subjected the sun and the moon, each orbiting for an appointed term. He is truly the Almighty, Most Forgiving"
  39,6,"He created you ňĻallňļ from a single soul,¬†then from it He made its mate.¬†And He produced for you four pairs of cattle.¬†He creates you in the wombs of your mothers ňĻin stagesňļ, one development after another, in three layers of darkness.¬†That is Allah‚ÄĒyour Lord! All authority belongs to Him. There is no god ňĻworthy of worshipňļ except Him. How can you then be turned away"
  39,7,"If you disbelieve, then ňĻknow thatňļ Allah is truly not in need of you, nor does He approve of disbelief from His servants. But if you become grateful ňĻthrough faithňļ, He will appreciate that from you. No soul burdened with sin will bear the burden of another. Then to your Lord is your return, and He will inform you of what you used to do. He certainly knows best what is ňĻhiddenňļ in the heart"
  39,8,"When one is touched with hardship, they cry out to their Lord, turning to Him ňĻaloneňļ. But as soon as He showers them with blessings from Him, they ňĻtotallyňļ forget the One they had cried to earlier, and set up equals to Allah to mislead ňĻothersňļ from His Way. Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúEnjoy your disbelief for a little while! You will certainly be one of the inmates of the Fire.‚ÄĚ"
  39,9,"ňĻAre they betterňļ or those who worship ňĻtheir Lordňļ devoutly in the hours of the night, prostrating and standing, fearing the Hereafter and hoping for the mercy of their Lord? Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúAre those who know equal to those who do not know?‚ÄĚ None will be mindful ňĻof thisňļ except people of reason"
  39,10,"Say ňĻO Prophet, that Allah saysňļ, ‚ÄúO My servants who believe! Be mindful of your Lord. Those who do good in this world will have a good reward. And Allah‚Äôs earth is spacious. Only those who endure patiently will be given their reward without limit.‚ÄĚ"
  39,11,"Say, ‚ÄúI am commanded to worship Allah, being sincerely devoted to Him ňĻaloneňļ"
  39,12,And I am commanded to be the first of those who submit ňĻto His Willňļ.‚ÄĚ
  39,13,"Say, ‚ÄúI truly fear‚ÄĒif I were to disobey my Lord‚ÄĒthe torment of a tremendous Day.‚ÄĚ"
  39,14,"Say, ‚ÄúIt is ňĻonlyňļ Allah that I worship, being sincere in my devotion to Him"
  39,15,"Worship then whatever ňĻgodsňļ you want instead of Him.‚ÄĚ Say, ‚ÄúThe ňĻtrueňļ losers are those who will lose themselves and their families on Judgment Day. That is indeed the clearest loss.‚ÄĚ"
  39,16,"They will have layers of fire above and below them. That is what Allah warns His servants with. So fear Me, O My servants"
  39,17,"And those who shun the worship of false gods, turning to Allah ňĻaloneňļ, will have good news. So give good news to My servants ňĻO Prophetňļ‚ÄĒ"
  39,18,"those who listen to what is said and follow the best of it.¬†These are the ones ňĻrightlyňļ guided by Allah, and these are ňĻtrulyňļ the people of reason"
  39,19,What about those against whom the decree of torment has been justified? Is it you ňĻO Prophetňļ who will then save those bound for the Fire
  39,20,"But those mindful of their Lord will have ňĻelevatedňļ mansions, built one above the other, under which rivers flow. ňĻThat isňļ the promise of Allah. ňĻAndňļ Allah never fails in ňĻHisňļ promise"
  39,21,"Do you not see that Allah sends down rain from the sky‚ÄĒchannelling it through streams in the earth‚ÄĒthen produces with it crops of various colours, then they dry up and you see them wither, and then He reduces them to chaff? Surely in this is a reminder for people of reason"
  39,22,"Can ňĻthe misguided be likeňļ those whose hearts Allah has opened to Islam, so they are enlightened by their Lord? So woe to those whose hearts are hardened at the remembrance of Allah! It is they who are clearly astray"
  39,23,"ňĻIt isňļ Allah ňĻWhoňļ has sent down the best message‚ÄĒa Book of perfect consistency and repeated lessons‚ÄĒwhich causes the skin ňĻand heartsňļ of those who fear their Lord to tremble, then their skin and hearts soften at the mention of ňĻthe mercy ofňļ Allah. That is the guidance of Allah, through which He guides whoever He wills. But whoever Allah leaves to stray will be left with no guide"
  39,24,"Are those who will only have their ňĻbareňļ faces to shield themselves from the awful torment on Judgment Day ňĻbetter than those in Paradiseňļ? It will ňĻthenňļ be said to the wrongdoers: ‚ÄúReap what you sowed!‚ÄĚ"
  39,25,"Those before them ňĻalsoňļ rejected ňĻthe truthňļ, then the torment came upon them from where they least expected"
  39,26,"So Allah made them taste humiliation in this worldly life, but far worse is the punishment of the Hereafter, if only they knew"
  39,27,"We have certainly set forth every ňĻkind ofňļ lesson for people in this Quran, so perhaps they will be mindful"
  39,28,"ňĻIt isňļ a Quran ňĻrevealedňļ in Arabic without any crookedness, so perhaps they will be conscious ňĻof Allahňļ"
  39,29,"Allah sets forth the parable of a slave owned by several quarrelsome masters, and a slave owned by only one master. Are they equal in condition?¬†Praise be to Allah! In fact, most of them do not know"
  39,30,"You ňĻO Prophetňļ will certainly die, and they will die too"
  39,31,Then on the Day of Judgment you will ňĻall settle yourňļ dispute before your Lord
  39,32,Who then does more wrong than those who lie about Allah and reject the truth after it has reached them? Is Hell not a ňĻfittingňļ home for the disbelievers
  39,33,And the one who has brought the truth and those who embrace it‚ÄĒit is they who are the righteous
  39,34,They will have whatever they desire with their Lord. That is the reward of the good-doers
  39,35,"As such, Allah will absolve them of ňĻevenňļ the worst of what they did and reward them according to the best of what they used to do"
  39,36,Is Allah not sufficient for His servant? Yet they threaten you with other ňĻpowerlessňļ gods besides Him! Whoever Allah leaves to stray will be left with no guide
  39,37,"And whoever Allah guides, none can lead astray. Is Allah not Almighty, capable of punishment"
  39,38,"If you ask them ňĻO Prophetňļ who created the heavens and the earth, they will certainly say, ‚ÄúAllah!‚ÄĚ Ask ňĻthemňļ, ‚ÄúConsider then whatever ňĻidolsňļ you invoke besides Allah: if it was Allah‚Äôs Will to harm me, could they undo that harm? Or if He willed ňĻsomeňļ mercy for me, could they withhold His mercy?‚ÄĚ Say, ‚ÄúAllah is sufficient for me. In Him ňĻaloneňļ the faithful put their trust.‚ÄĚ"
  39,39,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúO my people! Persist in your ways, for I ňĻtooňļ will persist in mine. You will soon come to know"
  39,40,who will be visited by a humiliating torment ňĻin this lifeňļ and overwhelmed by an everlasting punishment ňĻin the nextňļ.‚ÄĚ
  39,41,"Surely We have revealed to you the Book ňĻO Prophetňļ with the truth for humanity. So whoever chooses to be guided, it is for their own good. And whoever chooses to stray, it is only to their own loss. You are not a keeper over them"
  39,42,"ňĻIt isňļ Allah ňĻWhoňļ calls back the souls ňĻof peopleňļ upon their death as well as ňĻthe soulsňļ of the living during their sleep. Then He keeps those for whom He has ordained death, and releases the others until ňĻtheirňļ appointed time. Surely in this are signs for people who reflect"
  39,43,"Or have they taken others besides Allah as intercessors? Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúňĻWould they do so,ňļ even though those ňĻidolsňļ have neither authority nor intelligence?‚ÄĚ"
  39,44,"Say, ‚ÄúAll intercession belongs to Allah ňĻaloneňļ. To Him belongs the kingdom of the heavens and the earth. Then to Him you will ňĻallňļ be returned.‚ÄĚ"
  39,45,"Yet when Allah alone is mentioned, the hearts of those who disbelieve in the Hereafter are filled with disgust. But as soon as those ňĻgodsňļ other than Him are mentioned, they are filled with joy"
  39,46,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúO Allah‚ÄĒOriginator of the heavens and the earth, Knower of the seen and unseen! You will judge between Your servants regarding their differences.‚ÄĚ"
  39,47,"Even if the wrongdoers were to possess everything in the world twice over, they would certainly offer it to ransom themselves from the horrible punishment on Judgment Day, for they will see from Allah what they had never expected"
  39,48,"And the evil ňĻconsequencesňļ of their deeds will unfold before them, and they will be overwhelmed by what they used to ridicule"
  39,49,"When one is touched with hardship, they cry out to Us ňĻaloneňļ. Then when We shower Our blessings upon them, they say, ‚ÄúI have been granted all this only because of ňĻmyňļ knowledge.‚ÄĚ Not at all! It is ňĻno more thanňļ a test. But most of them do not know"
  39,50,"The same had already been said by those ňĻdestroyedňļ before them,¬†but their ňĻworldlyňļ gains were of no benefit to them"
  39,51,So the evil ňĻconsequencesňļ of their deeds overtook them. And the wrongdoers among these ňĻpagansňļ will be overtaken by the evil ňĻconsequencesňļ of their deeds. And they will have no escape
  39,52,Do they not know that Allah gives abundant or limited provisions to whoever He wills? Surely in this are signs for people who believe
  39,53,"Say, ňĻO Prophet, that Allah says,ňļ ‚ÄúO My servants who have exceeded the limits against their souls! Do not lose hope in Allah‚Äôs mercy, for Allah certainly forgives all sins.¬†He is indeed the All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  39,54,"Turn to your Lord ňĻin repentanceňļ, and ňĻfullyňļ submit to Him before the punishment reaches you, ňĻforňļ then you will not be helped"
  39,55,"Follow ňĻthe Quran,ňļ the best of what has been revealed to you from your Lord, before the punishment takes you by surprise while you are unaware"
  39,56,"so that no ňĻsinfulňļ soul will say ňĻon Judgment Dayňļ, ‚ÄėWoe to me for neglecting ňĻmy duties towardsňļ Allah, while ridiculing ňĻthe truthňļ.‚Äô"
  39,57,"Or ňĻa soul willňļ say, ‚ÄėIf only Allah had guided me, I would have certainly been one of the righteous.‚Äô"
  39,58,"Or say, upon seeing the torment, ‚ÄėIf only I had a second chance, I would have been one of the good-doers.‚Äô"
  39,59,"Not at all! My revelations had already come to you, but you rejected them, acted arrogantly, and were one of the disbelievers.‚ÄĚ"
  39,60,On the Day of Judgment you will see those who lied about Allah with their faces gloomy. Is Hell not a ňĻfittingňļ home for the arrogant
  39,61,"And Allah will deliver those who were mindful ňĻof Himňļ to their place of ňĻultimateňļ triumph. No evil will touch them, nor will they grieve"
  39,62,"Allah is the Creator of all things, and He is the Maintainer of everything"
  39,63,"To Him belong the keys ňĻof the treasuriesňļ¬†of the heavens and the earth. As for those who rejected the signs of Allah, it is they who will be the ňĻtrueňļ losers"
  39,64,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúAre you urging me to worship ňĻanyoneňļ other than Allah, O ignorant ones?‚ÄĚ"
  39,65,"It has already been revealed to you‚ÄĒand to those ňĻprophetsňļ before you‚ÄĒthat if you associate others ňĻwith Allahňļ, your deeds will certainly be void and you will truly be one of the losers"
  39,66,"Rather, worship Allah ňĻaloneňļ and be one of the grateful"
  39,67,"They have not shown Allah His proper reverence‚ÄĒwhen on the Day of Judgment the ňĻwholeňļ earth will be in His Grip, and the heavens will be rolled up in His Right Hand. Glorified and Exalted is He above what they associate ňĻwith Himňļ"
  39,68,"The Trumpet will be blown and all those in the heavens and all those on the earth will fall dead, except those Allah wills ňĻto spareňļ. Then it will be blown again and they will rise up at once, looking on ňĻin anticipationňļ"
  39,69,"The earth¬†will shine with the light of its Lord, the record ňĻof deedsňļ will be laid ňĻopenňļ, the prophets and the witnesses will be brought forward‚ÄĒand judgment will be passed on all with fairness. None will be wronged"
  39,70,"Every soul will be paid in full for its deeds, for Allah knows best what they have done"
  39,71,"Those who disbelieved will be driven to Hell in ňĻsuccessiveňļ groups. When they arrive there, its gates will be opened and its keepers will ask them: ‚ÄúDid messengers not come to you from among yourselves, reciting to you the revelations of your Lord and warning you of the coming of this Day of yours?‚ÄĚ The disbelievers will cry, ‚ÄúYes ňĻindeedňļ! But the decree of torment has come to pass against the disbelievers.‚ÄĚ"
  39,72,"It will be said to them, ‚ÄúEnter the gates of Hell, to stay there forever.‚ÄĚ What an evil home for the arrogant"
  39,73,"And those who were mindful of their Lord will be led to Paradise in ňĻsuccessiveňļ groups. When they arrive at its ňĻalreadyňļ open gates, its keepers will say, ‚ÄúPeace be upon you! You have done well, so come in, to stay forever.‚ÄĚ"
  39,74,"The righteous will say, ‚ÄúPraise be to Allah Who has fulfilled His promise to us, and made us inherit the ňĻeverlastingňļ land¬†to settle in Paradise wherever we please.‚ÄĚ How excellent is the reward of those who work ňĻrighteousnessňļ"
  39,75,"You will see the angels all around the Throne, glorifying the praises of their Lord, for judgment will have been passed on all with fairness. And it will be said,¬†‚ÄúPraise be to Allah‚ÄĒLord of all worlds!‚ÄĚ"
  40,1,Šł§√Ę-Mń©m
  40,2,"The revelation of this Book is from Allah‚ÄĒthe Almighty, All-Knowing"
  40,3,"the Forgiver of sin and Accepter of repentance, the Severe in punishment, and Infinite in bounty. There is no god ňĻworthy of worshipňļ except Him. To Him ňĻaloneňļ is the final return"
  40,4,"None disputes the signs of Allah except the disbelievers, so do not be deceived by their prosperity throughout the land"
  40,5,"Before them, the people of Noah denied ňĻthe truthňļ, as did ňĻotherňļ enemy forces afterwards. Every community plotted against its prophet to seize him, and argued in falsehood, ňĻhopingňļ to discredit the truth with it. So I seized them. And how ňĻhorribleňļ was My punishment"
  40,6,And so your Lord‚Äôs decree has been proven true against the disbelievers‚ÄĒthat they will be the inmates of the Fire
  40,7,"Those ňĻangelsňļ who carry the Throne and those around it glorify the praises of their Lord, have faith in Him, and seek forgiveness for the believers, ňĻpraying:ňļ ‚ÄúOur Lord! You encompass everything in ňĻYourňļ mercy and knowledge. So forgive those who repent and follow Your Way, and protect them from the torment of the Hellfire"
  40,8,"Our Lord! Admit them into the Gardens of Eternity which You have promised them, along with the righteous among their parents, spouses, and descendants. You ňĻaloneňļ are truly the Almighty, All-Wise"
  40,9,And protect them from ňĻthe consequences of theirňļ evil deeds. For whoever You protect from the evil of their deeds on that Day will have been shown Your mercy. That is ňĻtrulyňļ the ultimate triumph.‚ÄĚ
  40,10,"Indeed, it will be announced to the disbelievers, ‚ÄúAllah‚Äôs contempt for you‚ÄĒas you disbelieved when invited to belief‚ÄĒwas far worse than your contempt for one another ňĻTodayňļ.‚ÄĚ"
  40,11,"They will plead, ‚ÄúOur Lord! You made us lifeless twice, and gave us life twice.¬†Now we confess our sins. So is there any way out?‚ÄĚ"
  40,12,"ňĻThey will be told,ňļ ‚ÄúňĻNo!ňļ This is because when Allah alone was invoked, you ňĻstaunchlyňļ disbelieved. But when others were associated with Him ňĻin worshipňļ, you ňĻreadilyňļ believed. So ňĻTodayňļ judgment belongs to Allah ňĻaloneňļ‚ÄĒthe Most High, All-Great.‚ÄĚ"
  40,13,He is the One Who shows you His signs and sends down ňĻrain asňļ a provision for you from the sky. ňĻButňļ none will be mindful except those who turn ňĻto Himňļ
  40,14,"So call upon Allah with sincere devotion, even to the dismay of the disbelievers"
  40,15,"ňĻHe isňļ Highly Exalted in rank, Lord of the Throne. He sends down the revelation by His command to whoever He wills of His servants to warn ňĻallňļ of the Day of Meeting‚ÄĒ"
  40,16,"the Day all will appear ňĻbefore Allahňļ. Nothing about them will be hidden from Him. ňĻHe will ask,ňļ ‚ÄúWho does all authority belong to this Day? To Allah‚ÄĒthe One, the Supreme"
  40,17,Today every soul will be rewarded for what it has done. No injustice Today! Surely Allah is swift in reckoning.‚ÄĚ
  40,18,"Warn them ňĻO Prophetňļ of the approaching Day when the hearts will jump into the throats, suppressing distress. The wrongdoers will have neither a close friend nor intercessor to be heard"
  40,19,Allah ňĻevenňļ knows the sly glances of the eyes and whatever the hearts conceal
  40,20,"And Allah judges with the truth, while those ňĻidolsňļ they invoke besides Him cannot judge at all. Indeed, Allah ňĻaloneňļ is the All-Hearing, All-Seeing"
  40,21,"Have they not travelled throughout the land to see what was the end of those ňĻdestroyedňļ before them? They were far superior in might and ňĻricher inňļ monuments throughout the land. But Allah seized them for their sins, and they had no protector from Allah"
  40,22,"That was because their messengers used to come to them with clear proofs, but they persisted in disbelief. So Allah seized them. Surely He is All-Powerful, severe in punishment"
  40,23,"Indeed, We sent Moses with Our signs and compelling proof"
  40,24,"to Pharaoh, Ham√Ęn, and Korah. But they responded: ‚ÄúMagician! Total liar!‚ÄĚ"
  40,25,"Then, when he came to them with the truth from Us, they said, ‚ÄúKill the sons of those who believe with him and keep their women.‚ÄĚ But the plotting of the disbelievers was only in vain"
  40,26,"And Pharaoh said, ‚ÄúLet me kill Moses, and let him call upon his Lord! I truly fear that he may change your traditions or cause mischief in the land.‚ÄĚ"
  40,27,"Moses replied, ‚ÄúI seek refuge in my Lord and your Lord from every arrogant person who does not believe in the Day of Reckoning.‚ÄĚ"
  40,28,"A believing man from Pharaoh‚Äôs people, who was hiding his faith, argued, ‚ÄúWill you kill a man¬†ňĻonlyňļ for saying: ‚ÄėMy Lord is Allah,‚Äô while he has in fact come to you with clear proofs from your Lord? If he is a liar, it will be to his own loss. But if he is truthful, then you will be afflicted with some of what he is threatening you with. Surely Allah does not guide whoever is a transgressor, a total liar"
  40,29,"O my people! Authority belongs to you today, reigning supreme in the land. But who would help us against the torment of Allah, if it were to befall us?‚ÄĚ Pharaoh assured ňĻhis peopleňļ, ‚ÄúI am telling you only what I believe, and I am leading you only to the way of guidance.‚ÄĚ"
  40,30,"And the man who believed cautioned, ‚ÄúO my people! I truly fear for you the doom of ňĻearlierňļ enemy forces‚ÄĒ"
  40,31,"like the fate of the people of Noah, ‚Äô»ād, Tham√Ľd, and those after them. For Allah would never will to wrong ňĻHisňļ servants"
  40,32,O my people! I truly fear for you the Day all will be crying out ňĻto each otherňļ‚ÄĒ
  40,33,"the Day you will ňĻtry in vain toňļ turn your backs and run away, with no one to protect you from Allah. And whoever Allah leaves to stray will be left with no guide"
  40,34,"Joseph already came to you¬†earlier with clear proofs, yet you never ceased to doubt what he came to you with. When he died you said, ‚ÄėAllah will never send a messenger after him.‚Äô This is how Allah leaves every transgressor and doubter to stray‚ÄĒ"
  40,35,those who dispute Allah‚Äôs signs with no proof given to them. How despicable is that for Allah and the believers! This is how Allah seals the heart of every arrogant tyrant.‚ÄĚ
  40,36,"Pharaoh ordered, ‚ÄúO Ham√Ęn! Build me a high tower so I may reach the pathways"
  40,37,"leading up to the heavens and look for the God of Moses, although I am sure he is a liar.‚ÄĚ¬†And so Pharaoh‚Äôs evil deeds were made so appealing to him that he was hindered from the ňĻRightňļ Way. But the plotting of Pharaoh was only in vain"
  40,38,"And the man who believed urged, ‚ÄúO my people! Follow me, ňĻandňļ I will lead you to the Way of Guidance"
  40,39,"O my people! This worldly life is only ňĻa fleetingňļ enjoyment, whereas the Hereafter is truly the home of settlement"
  40,40,"Whoever does an evil deed will only be paid back with its equivalent. And whoever does good, whether male or female, and is a believer, they will enter Paradise, where they will be provided for without limit"
  40,41,"O my people! How is it that I invite you to salvation, while you invite me to the Fire"
  40,42,"You invite me to disbelieve in Allah and associate with Him what I have no knowledge of, while I invite you to the Almighty, Most Forgiving"
  40,43,"There is no doubt that whatever ňĻidolsňļ you invite me to ňĻworshipňļ are not worthy to be invoked either in this world or the Hereafter.¬†ňĻUndoubtedly,ňļ our return is to Allah, and the transgressors will be the inmates of the Fire"
  40,44,"You will remember what I say to you, and I entrust my affairs to Allah. Surely Allah is All-Seeing of all ňĻHisňļ servants.‚ÄĚ"
  40,45,So Allah protected him from the evil of their schemes. And Pharaoh‚Äôs people were overwhelmed by an evil punishment
  40,46,"they are exposed to the Fire ňĻin their gravesňļ morning and evening. And on the Day the Hour will be established ňĻit will be saidňļ, ‚ÄúAdmit Pharaoh‚Äôs people into the harshest punishment ňĻof Hellňļ.‚ÄĚ"
  40,47,"ňĻConsider the Dayňļ when they will dispute in the Fire, and the lowly ňĻfollowersňļ will appeal to the arrogant ňĻleadersňļ, ‚ÄúWe were your ňĻdedicatedňļ followers, will you then shield us from a portion of the Fire?‚ÄĚ"
  40,48,"The arrogant will say, ‚ÄúWe are all in it! ňĻForňļ Allah has already passed judgment over ňĻHisňļ servants.‚ÄĚ"
  40,49,"And those in the Fire will cry out to the keepers of Hell,¬†‚ÄúPray to your Lord to lighten the torment for us ňĻevenňļ for one day!‚ÄĚ"
  40,50,"The keepers will reply, ‚ÄúDid your messengers not ňĻconstantlyňļ come to you with clear proofs?‚ÄĚ They will say, ‚ÄúYes ňĻthey didňļ.‚ÄĚ The keepers will say, ‚ÄúThen pray! Though the prayer of the disbelievers is only in vain.‚ÄĚ"
  40,51,"We certainly help Our messengers and the believers, ňĻbothňļ in this worldly life and on the Day the witnesses will stand forth ňĻfor testimonyňļ‚ÄĒ"
  40,52,"the Day the wrongdoers‚Äô excuses will be of no benefit to them. They will be condemned, and will have the worst outcome"
  40,53,"And indeed, We gave Moses ňĻtrueňļ guidance, and made the Children of Israel inherit the Scripture‚ÄĒ"
  40,54,a guide and a reminder to people of reason
  40,55,"So be patient ňĻO Prophetňļ, ňĻforňļ Allah‚Äôs promise is certainly true. Seek forgiveness for your shortcomings.¬†And glorify the praises of your Lord morning and evening"
  40,56,"Surely those who dispute Allah‚Äôs signs‚ÄĒwith no proof given to them‚ÄĒhave nothing in their hearts but greed for dominance, which they will never attain. So seek refuge in Allah. Indeed, He alone is the All-Hearing, All-Seeing"
  40,57,"The creation of the heavens and the earth is certainly greater than the re-creation of humankind, but most people do not know"
  40,58,"Those blind ňĻto the truthňļ and those who can see are not equal, nor are those who believe and do good ňĻequalňļ to those who do evil. Yet you are hardly mindful"
  40,59,"The Hour is certainly coming, there is no doubt about it. But most people do not believe"
  40,60,"Your Lord has proclaimed, ‚ÄúCall upon Me, I will respond to you. Surely those who are too proud to worship Me will enter Hell, fully humbled.‚ÄĚ"
  40,61,"It is Allah Who has made the night for you to rest in and the day bright. Surely Allah is ever Bountiful to humanity, but most people are ungrateful"
  40,62,"That is Allah, your Lord, the Creator of all things. There is no god ňĻworthy of worshipňļ except Him. How can you then be deluded ňĻfrom the truthňļ"
  40,63,This is how those who used to reject Allah‚Äôs signs were ňĻalsoňļ deluded
  40,64,"It is Allah Who made the earth a place of settlement for you and the sky a canopy. He shaped you ňĻin the wombňļ, perfecting your form. And He has provided you with what is good and lawful. That is Allah‚ÄĒyour Lord. So Blessed is Allah, Lord of all worlds"
  40,65,"He is the Ever-Living. There is no god ňĻworthy of worshipňļ except Him. So call upon Him with sincere devotion, ňĻsaying,ňļ ‚ÄúAll praise is for Allah‚ÄĒLord of all worlds.‚ÄĚ"
  40,66,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúI have been forbidden to worship those ňĻidolsňļ you worship besides Allah, since clear proofs have come to me from my Lord. And I have been commanded to ňĻfullyňļ submit to the Lord of all worlds.‚ÄĚ"
  40,67,"He is the One Who created you¬†from dust, then from a sperm-drop,¬†then ňĻdeveloped you intoňļ a clinging clot ňĻof bloodňļ,¬†then He brings you forth as infants, so that you may reach your prime, and become old‚ÄĒthough some of you ňĻmayňļ die sooner‚ÄĒreaching an appointed time, so perhaps you may understand ňĻAllah‚Äôs powerňļ"
  40,68,"He is the One Who gives life and causes death. When He decrees a matter, He simply tells it, ‚ÄúBe!‚ÄĚ And it is"
