  41,24,"Even if they endure patiently, the Fire will ňĻalwaysňļ be their home. And if they ňĻbeg toňļ appease ňĻtheir Lordňļ, they will never be allowed to"
  41,25,"We placed at their disposal ňĻevilňļ associates who made their past and future ňĻmisdeedsňļ appealing to them.¬†ňĻSoňļ the fate of earlier communities of jinn and humans has been justified against them ňĻas wellňļ, ňĻforňļ they were truly losers"
  41,26,"The disbelievers advised ňĻone anotherňļ, ‚ÄúDo not listen to this Quran but drown it out so that you may prevail.‚ÄĚ"
