  41,28,"That is the reward of Allah‚Äôs enemies: the Fire, which will be their eternal home‚ÄĒa ňĻfittingňļ reward for their denial of Our revelations"
  41,29,"The disbelievers will ňĻthenňļ cry, ‚ÄúOur Lord! Show us those jinn and humans who led us astray: we will put them under our feet so that they will be among the lowest ňĻin Hellňļ.‚ÄĚ"
  41,30,"Surely those who say, ‚ÄúOur Lord is Allah,‚ÄĚ and then remain steadfast, the angels descend upon them,¬†ňĻsaying,ňļ ‚ÄúDo not fear, nor grieve. Rather, rejoice in the good news of Paradise, which you have been promised"
  41,31,"We are your supporters in this worldly life and in the Hereafter. There you will have whatever your souls desire, and there you will have whatever you ask for"
  41,32,"an accommodation from the All-Forgiving, Most Merciful ňĻLordňļ.‚ÄĚ"
  41,33,"And whose words are better than someone who calls ňĻothersňļ to Allah, does good, and says, ‚ÄúI am truly one of those who submit.‚ÄĚ"
  41,34,"Good and evil cannot be equal. Respond ňĻto evilňļ with what is best, then the one you are in a feud with will be like a close friend"
  41,35,But this cannot be attained except by those who are patient and who are truly fortunate
  41,36,"And if you are tempted by Satan, then seek refuge with Allah. Indeed, He ňĻaloneňļ is the All-Hearing, All-Knowing"
  41,37,"Among His signs are the day and the night, the sun and the moon. Do not prostrate to the sun or the moon, but prostrate to Allah, Who created them ňĻallňļ, if you ňĻtrulyňļ worship Him ňĻaloneňļ"
  41,38,"But if the pagans are too proud, then ňĻlet them know thatňļ those ňĻangelsňļ nearest to your Lord glorify Him day and night, and never grow weary"
  41,39,"And among His signs is that you see the earth devoid of life, but as soon as We send down rain upon it, it begins to stir ňĻto lifeňļ and swell. Indeed, the One Who revives it can easily revive the dead. He is certainly Most Capable of everything"
  41,40,"Indeed, those who abuse Our revelations¬†are not hidden from Us. Who is better: the one who will be cast into the Fire or the one who will be secure on Judgment Day? Do whatever you want. He is certainly All-Seeing of what you do"
  41,41,"Indeed, those who deny the Reminder¬†after it has come to them ňĻare doomedňļ, for it is truly a mighty Book"
  41,42,"It cannot be proven false from any angle. ňĻIt isňļ a revelation from the ňĻOne Who isňļ All-Wise, Praiseworthy"
  41,43,ňĻO Prophet!ňļ Nothing is said to you ňĻby the deniersňļ except what was already said to the messengers before you. Surely your Lord is ňĻthe Lordňļ of forgiveness and painful punishment
  41,44,"Had We revealed it as a non-Arabic Quran, they would have certainly argued, ‚ÄúIf only its verses were made clear ňĻin our languageňļ. What! A non-Arabic revelation for an Arab audience!‚ÄĚ Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúIt is a guide and a healing to the believers. As for those who disbelieve, there is deafness in their ears and blindness to it ňĻin their heartsňļ. It is as if they are being called from a faraway place.‚ÄĚ"
  41,45,"Indeed, We had given Moses the Scripture, but differences arose regarding it. Had it not been for a prior decree from your Lord,¬†their differences would have been settled ňĻat onceňļ. They are truly in alarming doubt about it"
  41,46,"Whoever does good, it is to their own benefit. And whoever does evil, it is to their own loss. Your Lord is never unjust to ňĻHisňļ creation"
  41,47,"With Him ňĻaloneňļ is the knowledge of the Hour. No fruit comes out of its husk, nor does a female conceive or deliver without His knowledge. And ňĻconsiderňļ the Day He will call to them, ‚ÄúWhere are My ňĻso-calledňļ associate-gods?‚ÄĚ They will cry, ‚ÄúWe declare before you that none of us testifies to that ňĻany longerňļ.‚ÄĚ"
  41,48,Whatever ňĻidolsňļ they used to invoke besides Allah will fail them. And they will realize that they will have no escape
  41,49,"One never tires of praying for good. And if touched with evil, they become desperate and hopeless"
  41,50,"And if We let them taste a mercy from Us after being touched with adversity, they will certainly say, ‚ÄúThis is what I deserve. I do not think the Hour will ňĻeverňļ come. And if in fact I am returned to my Lord, the finest reward with Him will definitely be mine.‚ÄĚ But We will surely inform the disbelievers of what they used to do. And We will certainly make them taste a harsh torment"
  41,51,"When We show favour to someone, they turn away, acting arrogantly. And when touched with evil, they make endless prayers ňĻfor goodňļ"
  41,52,"Ask ňĻthem, O Prophetňļ, ‚ÄúImagine if this ňĻQuranňļ is ňĻtrulyňļ from Allah and you deny it: who can be more astray than those who have gone too far in opposition ňĻto the truthňļ?‚ÄĚ"
  41,53,We will show them Our signs in the universe and within themselves until it becomes clear to them that this ňĻQuranňļ is the truth. Is it not enough that your Lord is a Witness over all things
  41,54,They are truly in doubt of the meeting with their Lord! ňĻButňļ He is indeed Fully Aware of everything
