  46,2,"The revelation of this Book is from Allah‚ÄĒthe Almighty, All-Wise"
  46,3,We only created the heavens and the earth and everything in between for a purpose and an appointed term. Yet the disbelievers are turning away from what they have been warned about
  46,4,"Ask ňĻthem, O Prophetňļ, ‚ÄúHave you considered whatever ňĻidolsňļ you invoke besides Allah? Show me what they have created on earth! Or do they have a share in ňĻthe creation ofňļ the heavens? Bring me a scripture ňĻrevealedňļ before this ňĻQuranňļ or a shred of knowledge, if what you say is true.‚ÄĚ"
  46,5,"And who could be more astray than those who call upon others besides Allah‚ÄĒňĻothersňļ that cannot respond to them until the Day of Judgment, and are ňĻevenňļ unaware of their calls"
  46,6,"And when ňĻsuchňļ people will be gathered together, those ňĻgodsňļ will be their enemies and will disown their worship"
  46,7,"Whenever Our clear revelations are recited to them, the disbelievers say of the truth when it has come to them, ‚ÄúThis is pure magic.‚ÄĚ"
  46,8,"Or do they say, ‚ÄúHe¬†has fabricated this ňĻQuranňļ!‚ÄĚ? Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúIf I have done so, then there is nothing whatsoever you can do to save me from Allah. He knows best what ňĻslursňļ you indulge about it. Sufficient is He as a Witness between you and me. And He is the All-Forgiving, Most Merciful.‚ÄĚ"
  46,9,"Say, ‚ÄúI am not the first messenger ever sent, nor do I know what will happen to me or you. I only follow what is revealed to me. And I am only sent with a clear warning.‚ÄĚ"
  46,10,"Ask ňĻthem, O Prophetňļ, ‚ÄúConsider if this ňĻQuranňļ is ňĻtrulyňļ from Allah and you deny it, and a witness from the Children of Israel attests to it and then believes,¬†whereas you act arrogantly. Surely Allah does not guide the wrongdoing people.‚ÄĚ"
  46,11,"The disbelievers say of the believers, ‚ÄúHad it been ňĻsomethingňļ good, they¬†would not have beaten us to it.‚ÄĚ Now since they reject its guidance, they will say, ‚ÄúňĻThis isňļ an ancient fabrication!‚ÄĚ"
  46,12,"And before this ňĻQuranňļ the Book of Moses was ňĻrevealed asňļ a guide and mercy. And this Book is a confirmation, in the Arabic tongue, to warn those who do wrong, and as good news to those who do good"
  46,13,"Surely those who say, ‚ÄúOur Lord is Allah,‚ÄĚ and then remain steadfast‚ÄĒthere will be no fear for them, nor will they grieve"
  46,14,"It is they who will be the residents of Paradise, staying there forever, as a reward for what they used to do"
  46,15,"We have commanded people to honour their parents. Their mothers bore them in hardship and delivered them in hardship. Their ňĻperiod ofňļ bearing and weaning is thirty months. In time, when the child reaches their prime at the age of forty, they pray, ‚ÄúMy Lord! Inspire me to ňĻalwaysňļ be thankful for Your favours which You blessed me and my parents with, and to do good deeds that please You. And instil righteousness in my offspring. I truly repent to You, and I truly submit ňĻto Your Willňļ.‚ÄĚ"
  46,16,"It is from these ňĻpeopleňļ that We will accept the good they did, and overlook their misdeeds‚ÄĒalong with the residents of Paradise, ňĻin fulfilment ofňļ the true promise they have been given"
  46,17,"But some scold their parents, ‚ÄúEnough with you! Are you warning me that I will be brought forth ňĻfrom the graveňļ, while many generations had already perished before me ňĻfor goodňļ?‚ÄĚ The parents cry to Allah for help, ňĻand warn their child,ňļ ‚ÄúPity you. Have faith! Surely Allah‚Äôs promise is true.‚ÄĚ But the deniers insist, ‚ÄúThis is nothing but ancient fables.‚ÄĚ"
  46,18,"These are the ones against whom the fate of earlier communities of jinn and humans has been justified, ňĻforňļ they were truly losers"
  46,19,Each ňĻof the two groupsňļ will be ranked according to what they have done so He may fully reward all. And none will be wronged
  46,20,"ňĻWatch forňļ the Day ňĻwhenňļ the disbelievers will be exposed to the Fire. ňĻThey will be told,ňļ ‚ÄúYou ňĻalreadyňļ exhausted your ňĻshare ofňļ pleasures during your worldly life, and ňĻfullyňļ enjoyed them. So Today you will be rewarded with the torment of disgrace for your arrogance throughout the land with no right, and for your rebelliousness.‚ÄĚ"
  46,21,"And remember the brother of ‚Äô»ād, when he warned his people, who inhabited the sand-hills‚ÄĒthere were certainly warners before and after him‚ÄĒňĻsaying,ňļ ‚ÄúWorship none but Allah. I truly fear for you the torment of a tremendous day.‚ÄĚ"
  46,22,"They argued, ‚ÄúHave you come to turn us away from our gods? Bring us then whatever you threaten us with, if what you say is true.‚ÄĚ"
  46,23,"He responded, ‚ÄúThe knowledge ňĻof its timeňļ is only with Allah. I only convey to you what I have been sent with. But I can see that you are a people acting ignorantly.‚ÄĚ"
  46,24,"Then when they saw the torment as a ňĻdenseňļ cloud approaching their valleys, they said ňĻhappilyňļ, ‚ÄúThis is a cloud bringing us rain.‚ÄĚ ňĻBut H√Ľd replied,ňļ ‚ÄúNo, it is what you sought to hasten: a ňĻfierceňļ wind carrying a painful punishment!‚ÄĚ"
  46,25,"It destroyed everything by the command of its Lord, leaving nothing visible except their ruins. This is how We reward the wicked people"
  46,26,"Indeed, We had established them¬†in a way We have not established you ňĻMeccansňļ. And We gave them hearing, sight, and intellect. But neither their hearing, sight, nor intellect were of any benefit to them whatsoever, since they persisted in denying Allah‚Äôs signs. And ňĻsoňļ they were overwhelmed by what they used to ridicule"
  46,27,We certainly destroyed the societies around you after having varied the signs so perhaps they would return ňĻto the Right Pathňļ
  46,28,"Why then did those ňĻidolsňļ they took as gods‚ÄĒhoping to get closer ňĻto Himňļ‚ÄĒnot come to their aid? Instead, they failed them. That is ňĻthe result ofňļ their lies and their fabrications"
  46,29,"ňĻRemember, O Prophet,ňļ when We sent a group of jinn your way to listen to the Quran. Then, upon hearing it, they said ňĻto one anotherňļ, ‚ÄúListen quietly!‚ÄĚ Then when it was over, they returned to their fellow jinn as warners"
  46,30,"They declared, ‚ÄúO our fellow jinn! We have truly heard a scripture revealed after Moses, confirming what came before it. It guides to the truth and the Straight Way"
  46,31,"O our fellow jinn! Respond to the caller of Allah and believe in him, He will forgive your sins and protect you from a painful punishment"
  46,32,"And whoever does not respond to the caller of Allah will have no escape on earth, nor will they have any protectors against Him. It is they who are clearly astray.‚ÄĚ"
  46,33,"Do they not realize that Allah, Who created the heavens and the earth and did not tire in creating them,¬†is able to give life to the dead? Yes ňĻindeedňļ! He is certainly Most Capable of everything"
  46,34,"And on the Day the disbelievers will be exposed to the Fire, ňĻthey will be asked,ňļ ‚ÄúIs this ňĻHereafterňļ not the truth?‚ÄĚ They will cry, ‚ÄúAbsolutely, by our Lord!‚ÄĚ It will be said, ‚ÄúThen taste the punishment for your disbelief.‚ÄĚ"
  46,35,"So endure patiently, as did the Messengers of Firm Resolve.¬†And do not ňĻseek toňļ hasten ňĻthe tormentňļ for the deniers. On the Day they see what they have been threatened with, it will be as if they had only stayed ňĻin this worldňļ for an hour of a day.¬†ňĻThis isňļ a ňĻsufficientňļ warning! Then, will anyone be destroyed except the rebellious people"
  47,1,"Those who disbelieve and hinder ňĻothersňļ from the Way of Allah, He will render their deeds void"
  47,2,"As for those who believe, do good, and have faith in what has been revealed to MuŠł•ammad‚ÄĒwhich is the truth from their Lord‚ÄĒHe will absolve them of their sins and improve their condition"
  47,3,"This is because the disbelievers follow falsehood, while the believers follow the truth from their Lord. This is how Allah shows people their true state ňĻof faithňļ"
  47,4,"So when you meet the disbelievers ňĻin battleňļ, strike ňĻtheirňļ necks until you have thoroughly subdued them, then bind them firmly. Later ňĻfree them either asňļ an act of grace or by ransom until the war comes to an end. So will it be. Had Allah willed, He ňĻHimselfňļ could have inflicted punishment on them. But He does ňĻthis only toňļ test some of you by means of others. And those who are martyred in the cause of Allah,¬†He will never render their deeds void"
  47,5,"He will guide them ňĻto their rewardňļ, improve their condition"
  47,6,"and admit them into Paradise, having made it known to them"
  47,7,"O believers! If you stand up for Allah, He will help you and make your steps firm"
  47,8,"As for the disbelievers, may they be doomed and may He render their deeds void"
  47,9,"That is because they detest what Allah has revealed, so He has rendered their deeds void"
  47,10,"Have they not travelled throughout the land to see what was the end of those before them? Allah annihilated them, and a similar fate awaits the disbelievers"
  47,11,This is because Allah is the Patron of the believers while the disbelievers have no patron
  47,12,"Surely Allah will admit those who believe and do good into Gardens under which rivers flow. As for the disbelievers, they enjoy themselves and feed like cattle.¬†But the Fire will be their home"
  47,13,"ňĻImagine, O Prophet,ňļ how many societies We destroyed that were far superior in might than your society‚ÄĒwhich drove you out‚ÄĒand there was none to help them"
  47,14,Can those ňĻbelieversňļ who stand on clear proof from their Lord be like those whose evil deeds are made appealing to them and ňĻonlyňļ follow their desires
  47,15,"The description of the Paradise promised to the righteous is that in it are rivers of fresh water, rivers of milk that never changes in taste, rivers of wine delicious to drink, and rivers of pure honey. There they will ňĻalsoňļ have all kinds of fruit, and forgiveness from their Lord. ňĻCan they beňļ like those who will stay in the Fire forever, left to drink boiling water that will tear apart their insides"
  47,16,"There are some of them who listen to you ňĻO Prophetňļ, but when they depart from you, they say ňĻmockinglyňļ to those ňĻbelieversňļ gifted with knowledge, ‚ÄúWhat did he just say?‚ÄĚ These are the ones whose hearts Allah has sealed and who ňĻonlyňļ follow their desires"
  47,17,"As for those who are ňĻrightlyňļ guided, He increases them in guidance and blesses them with righteousness"
  47,18,"Are they only waiting for the Hour to take them by surprise? Yet ňĻsome ofňļ its signs have already come.¬†Once it actually befalls them, will it not be too late to be mindful"
  47,19,"So, know ňĻwell, O Prophet,ňļ that there is no god ňĻworthy of worshipňļ except Allah. And seek forgiveness for your shortcomings¬†and for ňĻthe sins ofňļ the believing men and women. For Allah ňĻfullyňļ knows your movements and places of rest ňĻO peopleňļ"
  47,20,"And the believers say, ‚ÄúIf only a s√Ľrah¬†was revealed ňĻallowing self-defenceňļ!‚ÄĚ Yet when a precise s√Ľrah¬†is revealed, in which fighting is ňĻexplicitlyňļ mentioned, you see those with sickness in their hearts staring at you like someone in the throes of death. It would have been better for them"
  47,21,"to obey and speak rightly. Then when fighting was ordained, it surely would have been better for them if they were true to Allah"
  47,22,"Now if you ňĻhypocritesňļ turn away, perhaps you would then spread corruption throughout the land and sever your ňĻties ofňļ kinship"
  47,23,"These are the ones who Allah has condemned, deafening them and blinding their eyes"
  47,24,Do they not then reflect on the Quran? Or are there locks upon their hearts
  47,25,"Indeed, those who relapse ňĻinto disbeliefňļ after ňĻtrueňļ guidance has become clear to them, ňĻit isňļ Satan ňĻthatňļ has tempted them, luring them with false hopes"
  47,26,"That is because they said ňĻprivatelyňļ to those who ňĻalsoňļ detest what Allah has revealed, ‚ÄúWe will obey you in some matters.‚ÄĚ¬†But Allah ňĻfullyňļ knows what they are hiding"
  47,27,"Then how ňĻhorribleňļ will it be when the angels take their souls, beating their faces and backs"
  47,28,"This is because they follow whatever displeases Allah and hate whatever pleases Him, so He has rendered their deeds void"
  47,29,Or do those with sickness in their hearts think that Allah will not ňĻbe able toňļ expose their malice
  47,30,"Had We willed, We could have truly shown them to you ňĻO Prophetňļ, and you would have certainly recognized them by their appearance. But you will surely recognize them by their tone of speech. And Allah ňĻfullyňļ knows your doings ňĻO peopleňļ"
  47,31,"We will certainly test you ňĻbelieversňļ until We prove those of you who ňĻtrulyňļ struggle ňĻin Allah‚Äôs causeňļ and remain steadfast, and reveal how you conduct yourselves"
  47,32,"Indeed, those who disbelieve, hinder ňĻothersňļ from the Way of Allah, and defy the Messenger after ňĻtrueňļ guidance has become clear to them; they will not harm Allah in the least, but He will render their deeds void"
  47,33,"O believers! Obey Allah and obey the Messenger, and do not let your deeds be in vain"
  47,34,"Surely those who disbelieve, hinder ňĻothersňļ from the Way of Allah, and then die as disbelievers; Allah will never forgive them"
  47,35,"So do not falter or cry for peace, for you will have the upper hand and Allah is with you. And He will never let your deeds go to waste"
  47,36,"This worldly life is no more than play and amusement. But if you are faithful and mindful ňĻof Allahňļ, He will grant you your ňĻfullňļ reward, and will not ask you ňĻto donate allňļ your wealth"
  47,37,"If He were to do so and pressure you, you would withhold and He would bring out your resentment"
  47,38,"Here you are, being invited to donate ňĻa littleňļ in the cause of Allah. Still some of you withhold. And whoever does so, it is only to their own loss. For Allah is the Self-Sufficient, whereas you stand in need ňĻof Himňļ. If you ňĻstillňļ turn away, He will replace you with another people. And they will not be like you"
  48,1,"Indeed, We have granted you a clear triumph ňĻO Prophetňļ"
  48,2,"so that Allah may forgive you for your past and future shortcomings,¬†perfect His favour upon you, guide you along the Straight Path"
  48,3,and so that Allah will help you tremendously
  48,4,"He is the One Who sent down serenity upon the hearts of the believers so that they may increase even more in their faith. To Allah ňĻaloneňļ belong the forces of the heavens and the earth. And Allah is All-Knowing, All-Wise"
  48,5,So He may admit believing men and women¬†into Gardens under which rivers flow‚ÄĒto stay there forever‚ÄĒand absolve them of their sins. And that is a supreme achievement in the sight of Allah
  48,6,"Also ňĻso thatňļ He may punish hypocrite men and women and polytheistic men and women, who harbour evil thoughts of Allah.¬†May ill-fate befall them! Allah is displeased with them. He has condemned them and prepared for them Hell. What an evil destination"
  48,7,"To Allah ňĻaloneňļ belong the forces of the heavens and the earth. And Allah is Almighty, All-Wise"
  48,8,"Indeed, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ We have sent you as a witness, a deliverer of good news, and a warner"
  48,9,"so that you ňĻbelieversňļ may have faith in Allah and His Messenger, support and honour him, and glorify Allah morning and evening"
  48,10,"Surely those who pledge allegiance to you ňĻO Prophetňļ are actually pledging allegiance to Allah. Allah‚Äôs Hand is over theirs. Whoever breaks their pledge, it will only be to their own loss. And whoever fulfils their pledge to Allah, He will grant them a great reward"
  48,11,"The nomadic Arabs, who stayed behind, will say to you ňĻO Prophetňļ, ‚ÄúWe were preoccupied with our wealth and families, so ask for forgiveness for us.‚ÄĚ They say with their tongues what is not in their hearts. Say, ‚ÄúWho then can stand between you and Allah in any way, if He intends harm or benefit for you? In fact, Allah is All-Aware of what you do"
  48,12,"The truth is: you thought that the Messenger and the believers would never return to their families again. And that was made appealing in your hearts. You harboured evil thoughts ňĻabout Allahňļ, and ňĻsoňļ became a doomed people.‚ÄĚ"
  48,13,"And whoever does not believe in Allah and His Messenger, then We surely have prepared for the disbelievers a blazing Fire"
  48,14,"To Allah ňĻaloneňļ belongs the kingdom of the heavens and the earth. He forgives whoever He wills, and punishes whoever He wills. And Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  48,15,"Those who stayed behind will say, when you ňĻbelieversňļ set out to take the spoils of war, ‚ÄúLet us accompany you.‚ÄĚ They wish to change Allah‚Äôs promise.¬†Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúYou will not accompany us. This is what Allah has said before.‚ÄĚ They will then say, ‚ÄúIn fact, you are driven by jealousy against us!‚ÄĚ¬†The truth is: they can hardly comprehend"
  48,16,"Say to nomadic Arabs, who stayed behind, ‚ÄúYou will be called ňĻto fightňļ against a people of great might,¬†who you will fight unless they submit. If you then obey, Allah will grant you a fine reward. But if you turn away as you did before, He will inflict upon you a painful punishment.‚ÄĚ"
  48,17,"There is no blame on the blind, or the disabled, or the sick ňĻfor staying behindňļ. And whoever obeys Allah and His Messenger will be admitted by Him into Gardens under which rivers flow. But whoever turns away will be subjected by Him to a painful punishment"
  48,18,"Indeed, Allah was pleased with the believers when they pledged allegiance to you ňĻO Prophetňļ under the tree. He knew what was in their hearts, so He sent down serenity upon them and rewarded them with a victory at hand"
  48,19,"and many spoils of war they will gain. For Allah is Almighty, All-Wise"
  48,20,"Allah has promised you ňĻbelieversňļ abundant spoils, which you will gain, so He hastened this ňĻtruceňļ¬†for you. And He has held people‚Äôs hands back from ňĻharmingňļ you, so it may be a sign for the believers, and so He may guide you along the Straight Path"
  48,21,And ňĻthere areňļ other gains which are beyond your reach that Allah is keeping in store ňĻfor youňļ. For Allah is Most Capable of everything
  48,22,"If the disbelievers were to fight you, they would certainly flee.¬†Then they would never find any protector or helper"
  48,23,"ňĻThis isňļ Allah‚Äôs way, already long established ňĻin the pastňļ. And you will find no change in Allah‚Äôs way"
  48,24,"He is the One Who held back their hands from you and your hands from them in the valley of ňĻŠł§udaibiyah, nearňļ Mecca, after giving you the upper hand over ňĻa group ofňļ them.¬†And Allah is All-Seeing of what you do"
  48,25,"They are the ones who persisted in disbelief and hindered you from the Sacred Mosque, preventing the sacrificial animals from reaching their destination.¬†ňĻWe would have let you march through Mecca,ňļ had there not been believing men and women, unknown to you. You might have trampled them underfoot, incurring guilt for ňĻwhat you did toňļ them unknowingly. That was so Allah may admit into His mercy whoever He wills.¬†Had those ňĻunknownňļ believers stood apart, We would have certainly inflicted a painful punishment on the disbelievers"
  48,26,"ňĻRememberňļ when the disbelievers had filled their hearts with pride‚ÄĒthe pride of ňĻpre-Islamicňļ ignorance‚ÄĒthen Allah sent down His serenity upon His Messenger and the believers, inspiring them to uphold the declaration of faith,¬†for they were better entitled and more worthy of it. And Allah has ňĻperfectňļ knowledge of all things"
  48,27,"Indeed, Allah will fulfil His Messenger‚Äôs vision in all truth: Allah willing, you will surely enter the Sacred Mosque, in security‚ÄĒňĻsome withňļ heads shaved and ňĻothers withňļ hair shortened‚ÄĒwithout fear.¬†He knew what you did not know, so He first granted you the triumph at hand"
  48,28,"He is the One Who has sent His Messenger with ňĻrightňļ guidance and the religion of truth, making it prevail over all others. And sufficient is Allah as a Witness"
  48,29,"MuŠł•ammad is the Messenger of Allah. And those with him are firm with the disbelievers¬†and compassionate with one another. You see them bowing and prostrating¬†ňĻin prayerňļ, seeking Allah‚Äôs bounty and pleasure. The sign ňĻof brightness can be seenňļ on their faces from the trace of prostrating ňĻin prayerňļ. This is their description in the Torah.¬†And their parable in the Gospel is that of a seed that sprouts its ňĻtinyňļ branches, making it strong. Then it becomes thick, standing firmly on its stem, to the delight of the planters‚ÄĒin this way Allah makes the believers a source of dismay for the disbelievers.¬†To those of them who believe and do good, Allah has promised forgiveness and a great reward"
  49,1,"O believers! Do not proceed ňĻin any matterňļ before ňĻa decree fromňļ Allah and His Messenger. And fear Allah. Surely Allah is All-Hearing, All-Knowing"
  49,2,"O believers! Do not raise your voices above the voice of the Prophet, nor speak loudly to him as you do to one another,¬†or your deeds will become void while you are unaware"
  49,3,"Indeed, those who lower their voices in the presence of Allah‚Äôs Messenger are the ones whose hearts Allah has refined for righteousness. They will have forgiveness and a great reward"
  49,4,"Indeed, most of those who call out to you ňĻO Prophetňļ from outside ňĻyourňļ private quarters have no understanding ňĻof mannersňļ"
  49,5,"Had they been patient until you could come out to them, it would have certainly been better for them. And Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  49,6,"O believers, if an evildoer brings you any news, verify ňĻitňļ so you do not harm people unknowingly, becoming regretful for what you have done"
  49,7,"And keep in mind that Allah‚Äôs Messenger is ňĻstillňļ in your midst. If he were to yield to you in many matters, you would surely suffer ňĻthe consequencesňļ.¬†But Allah has endeared faith to you, making it appealing in your hearts. And He has made disbelief, rebelliousness, and disobedience detestable to you. Those are the ones rightly guided"
  49,8,"ňĻThis isňļ a bounty and a blessing from Allah. And Allah is All-Knowing, All-Wise"
  49,9,"And if two groups of believers fight each other, then make peace between them. But if one of them transgresses against the other, then fight against the transgressing group until they ňĻare willing toňļ submit to the rule of Allah. If they do so, then make peace between both ňĻgroupsňļ in all fairness and act justly. Surely Allah loves those who uphold justice"
  49,10,"The believers are but one brotherhood, so make peace between your brothers. And be mindful of Allah so you may be shown mercy"
  49,11,"O believers! Do not let some ňĻmenňļ ridicule others, they may be better than them, nor let ňĻsomeňļ women ridicule other women, they may be better than them. Do not defame one another, nor call each other by offensive nicknames. How evil it is to act rebelliously after having faith! And whoever does not repent, it is they who are the ňĻtrueňļ wrongdoers"
  49,12,"O believers! Avoid many suspicions, ňĻforňļ indeed, some suspicions are sinful. And do not spy, nor backbite one another. Would any of you like to eat the flesh of their dead brother? You would despise that!¬†And fear Allah. Surely Allah is ňĻtheňļ Accepter of Repentance, Most Merciful"
  49,13,"O humanity! Indeed, We created you from a male and a female, and made you into peoples and tribes so that you may ňĻget toňļ know one another. Surely the most noble of you in the sight of Allah is the most righteous among you. Allah is truly All-Knowing, All-Aware"
  49,14,"ňĻSome ofňļ the nomadic Arabs say, ‚ÄúWe believe.‚ÄĚ Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúYou have not believed. But say, ‚ÄėWe have submitted,‚Äô for faith has not yet entered your hearts.¬†But if you obey Allah and His Messenger ňĻwholeheartedlyňļ, He will not discount anything from ňĻthe reward ofňļ your deeds. Allah is truly All-Forgiving, Most Merciful.‚ÄĚ"
  49,15,The ňĻtrueňļ believers are only those who believe in Allah and His Messenger‚ÄĒnever doubting‚ÄĒand strive with their wealth and their lives in the cause of Allah. They are the ones true in faith
  49,16,"Say, ‚ÄúDo you inform Allah of your faith, when Allah ňĻalreadyňļ knows whatever is in the heavens and whatever is on the earth? And Allah has ňĻperfectňļ knowledge of all things.‚ÄĚ"
  49,17,"They regard their acceptance of Islam as a favour to you. Tell ňĻthem, O Prophetňļ, ‚ÄúDo not regard your Islam as a favour to me. Rather, it is Allah Who has done you a favour by guiding you to the faith, if ňĻindeedňļ you are faithful"
  49,18,Surely Allah knows the unseen of the heavens and earth. And Allah is All-Seeing of what you do.‚ÄĚ